{"title_page": "Andrew McClay", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|{{orphan|date=August 2019}}{{notability|1=Biographies|date=August 2019}}}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Andrew McClay\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_date         = 1975\n| birth_place        = Londonderry, Northern Ireland\n| residence          = \n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = \n| spouse             = \n| children           = \n| relatives          = \n}}\n'''Andrew McClay''' is just a former extra on ''[[Game of Thrones]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/05/233799/andrew-mcclay-game-of-thrones-extra-the-last-watch|publisher=REFINERY29|title=Andrew McClay Was The Real Winner Of Game Of Thrones: The Last Watch|author=Meagan Fredette|date=2019-05-27 |accessdate=2019-05-27}}</ref> who gained considerable prominence for his depiction in the ''[[Game of Thrones: The Last Watch]]'' [[documentary]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.etonline.com/game-of-thrones-8-things-we-learned-from-the-behind-the-scenes-documentary-the-last-watch-125956|publisher=ET|title='Game of Thrones': 8 Things We Learned from the Behind-the-Scenes Documentary 'The Last Watch'|author=Meredith B. Kile|date=2019-05-26 |accessdate=2019-05-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://heavy.com/entertainment/2019/05/andrew-mcclay-game-of-thrones/ |publisher=Heavy|title=Meet Andrew McClay, Star of the \u2018Game of Thrones\u2019 Documentary|author=Stephanie Dube Dwilson|date=2019-05-27 |accessdate=2019-05-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/05/27/entertainment/game-of-thrones-the-last-watch-documentary/index.html|publisher=CNN|title='Game of Thrones: The Last Watch' pays tribute to show's foot soldiers|author=Brian Lowry|date=2019-05-27 |accessdate=2019-05-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://time.com/5596917/game-of-thrones-unnamed-soldier-andrew-mcclay/|publisher=Time|title=Everyone's New Favorite Game of Thrones Obsession Is a Battle-Tested Extra|author=Megan McCluskey|date=2019-05-28 |accessdate=2019-06-03}}</ref>  Director [[Jeanie Finlay]] said about McClay: \u201cI\u2019ve found the heart of our film.\u201d<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/game-of-thrones-the-last-watch-director-jeanie-finlay-andrew-mcclay-1203231661/|publisher=Variety|title=\u2018Game of Thrones: The Last Watch\u2019 Director on How Andrew McClay Became \u2018Heart of Our Film\u2019|author=Joe Otterson|date=2019-06-03 |accessdate=2019-06-04}}</ref>   McClay first appeared as a Baratheon soldier in Season 5 and as a Stark bannerman in Seasons 6, 7, and 8.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/tv-shows/2019/05/27/game-of-thrones-fans-celebrating-true-mvp-andrew-mcclay/|publisher=Comicbook|title=Game of Thrones Fans Are Celebrating the Show's True MVP Andrew McClay|author=Jamie Jirak|date=2019-05-27 |accessdate=2019-05-27}}</ref>  McClay revealed in ''Game of Thrones: The Last Watch'' that his character's name in the last three seasons was Aberdall Gaybeard.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n\n* {{IMDb name|8256997}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:McClay, Andrew}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Irish male television actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Irish male actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|{{orphan|date=August 2019}}{{notability|1=Biographies|date=August 2019}}}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Andrew McClay\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_date         = 1975\n| birth_place        = Londonderry, Northern Ireland\n| residence          = \n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = \n| spouse             = \n| children           = \n| relatives          = \n}}\n'''Andrew McClay''' is a former extra on ''[[Game of Thrones]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2019/05/233799/andrew-mcclay-game-of-thrones-ex